http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/KCR%E2%80%99s-visit-to-Warangal-raises-hopes/article13978159.ece

Warangal residents are eagerly awaiting the visit of Chief Minister K. Chandrasekhar Rao, who is expected to shower sops enthused by the massive mandate the party MP, P. Dayakar, got in the recent by-election.Soon after the result was out, the Chief Minister promised to develop Warangal in return for peoples’ continued patronage to the party.According to the tentative schedule, the Chief Minister would arrive at Komuravelli village in Cheriyal mandal to take part in the celestial wedding of Sri Mallikarjuna Swamy on January 3. He would return to Hyderabad the same day.On January 4, he would visit Hanamkonda along with Union Minister Nitin Gadkari. At Madikonda, they would inaugurate works on the proposed widening of the national highway between Bhongir and Warangal.They would also formally commission the Mullakatta bridge on river Godavari at Madikonda. Later, they would address a public meeting at the same venue.The Chief Minister would hold a review meeting with the district officials at the Collectorate in the evening.On January 5, he would leave for Bhupalpalli where he would dedicate to the nation a 600 MW power plant at Chelpur. He would return to Hanamkonda and would hold another review meeting with the officials.The Chief Minister is expected to review the arrangements being made for the ensuing Sammakka Sarakka Jatara, Two-Bedroom Housing Scheme, outer ring road, underground drainage, proposed integrated textile park among others.He would leave for Hyderabad on January 6, according to party sources.Deputy Chief Minister Kadiam Srihari and Tribal Welfare Minister A. Chandulal closeted with the officials discussing arrangements for the Chief Minister’s visit.